<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,259,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Remarks:</emphasis>
This specimen was received from Genoa in 1888 and is indicated as 
<emphasis box="[1027,1110,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">‘tipico’</emphasis>
in the accompanying list (see discussion of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salvadori" authorityYear="1876" box="[306,599,295,321]" class="Aves" family="Melanocharitidae" genus="Melanocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chloroptera">
<emphasis box="[306,599,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Melanocharis chloroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above). The original label is not present, only a replacement label that has been added at NHMO (
<figureCitation box="[417,530,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,787,811]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,186,761]" captionTargetId="figure-24@16.[149,1437,181,763]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Labels of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection described by T. Salvadori. a) Ptilotis erythropleura NHMO-BI-86778 (collector’s label); b) Melanocharis chloroptera NHMO-BI-61863 (NHMO label); c) Zosterops novae guineae NHMO-BI-86649 (NHMO label); d) Dicaeum misoriense NHMO-BI-61856 (collector’s label)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626777/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Figure 6c</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[551,741,331,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="317 - 347" refId="ref16359" refString="Salvadori, T. (1878) Descrizione di trentuna specie nuove di uccelli della sottoregione papuana, e note intorno ad altre poco conosciute. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 12, 317 - 347." type="journal article" year="1878">Salvadori (1878)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify an exact number of specimens in his original publication, but in 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[363,555,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, he listed 
<specimenCount box="[668,848,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
(
<emphasis box="[864,907,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">a–h</emphasis>
) as 
<typeStatus box="[953,1012,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">types</typeStatus>
of the species. Based on the information available on the current label, the NHMO specimen corresponds to specimen 
<emphasis box="[1077,1091,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">b</emphasis>
. Salvadori spelled the specific epithet in two words, 
<emphasis box="[391,571,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[395,467,439,465]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="novae">novae</taxonomicName>
guineae’
</emphasis>
, in both of the mentioned publications, but in accordance with article 32.5.2.2 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation author="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[297,985,475,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref14975" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 1999</bibRefCitation>
) it has later been changed to the current 
<emphasis box="[151,325,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">‘novaeguineae’</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
Three other 
<typeStatus box="[336,434,547,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">syntypes</typeStatus>
are in MSNG (C.E. 11526–11528; 
<bibRefCitation author="Arbocco, G. &amp; Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C." box="[830,1057,547,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="184 - 265" refId="ref13577" refString="Arbocco, G., Capocaccia, L. &amp; Violani, C. (1979) Catalogo dei tipi di uccelli del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 82, 184 - 265." type="journal article" year="1979">
Arbocco 
<emphasis box="[934,990,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">et al.</emphasis>
1979
</bibRefCitation>
), corresponding to specimens 
<emphasis box="[1396,1408,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">e</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1422,1436,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">g</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[199,213,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">h</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[250,442,583,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, and in MRSN specimen 
<emphasis box="[730,744,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">a</emphasis>
is registered as MZUT Av4174 (
<bibRefCitation author="Aimassi, G. &amp; Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L." box="[1114,1338,583,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="65 - 154" refId="ref13467" refString="Aimassi, G., Pulcher, C. &amp; Ghiraldi, L. (2020) Type specimens of birds in the Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali (Torino, Italy). Journal of the National Museum (Prague), Natural History Series, 189, 65 - 154. https: // doi. org / 10.37520 / jnmpnhs. 2020.007" type="journal article" year="2020">
Aimassi 
<emphasis box="[1215,1271,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
; Giorgio Aimassi, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
A fifth specimen is in RMNH (RMNH 90782, collected by Bruijn in Arfak, 
<date box="[1029,1213,655,681]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1876-01-30">30 January 1876</date>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dekker, R. W. R. J. &amp; Quaisser, C." pageId="19" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref14033" refString="Dekker, R. W. R. J. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2006) Type-specimens of birds in the National Museum of Natural History, Leiden. Part 3. Passerines: Pachycephalidae - Corvidae (Peters's sequence). NNM Technical Bulletin, 9, 1 - 77." type="journal article" year="2006">Dekker &amp; Quaisser 2006</bibRefCitation>
). This was not listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Salvadori, T." box="[482,674,691,717]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refId="ref16401" refString="Salvadori, T. (1881) Ornitologia della Papuasia e delle Molucche. Vol. 2. Stamperia Reale della ditta G. B. Paravia E Comp., Torino, 705 pp." type="book" year="1881">Salvadori (1881)</bibRefCitation>
, but as Salvadori in his original description wrote that he had examined several specimens collected by Beccari and Bruijn in the Arfak mountains, also this RMNH specimen must be considered part of the 
<typeStatus box="[402,450,763,789]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
